\details{
\code{AutoIML} orchestrates a gate-based interpretability workflow (G0A, G0B, G1-G6, G7A, G7B) for
\code{\link[mlr3:mlr3-package]{mlr3}} tasks and learners. It produces a reproducible
audit trail and data-/task-dependent interpretability artifacts.

Run the workflow with \verb{$run()}; inspect results with \verb{$overview()} and
\verb{$report_card()}; retrieve non-plot tables via \verb{$tables()}; and generate
ggplot2 outputs via \verb{$plot(type=...)}.
}
\examples{
library(mlr3)
task = tsk("penguins")
learner = lrn("classif.rpart", predict_type = "prob")
resampling = rsmp("cv", folds = 5)
auto = AutoIML$new(task = task, learner = learner, resampling = resampling,
  purpose = "global_insight", quick_start = FALSE, seed = 123)
result = auto$run(verbose = TRUE)
auto$report_card()
auto$tables("g2")
# auto$plot("g2_effect", feature = "body_mass", class_label = "Adelie")
}
\seealso{
\code{\link[=autoiml]{autoiml()}} for a functional wrapper.
}
